  "body": "Hi.\r\n\r\nI have the following code:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/morphex/ethereum-classic-taxman/blob/main/transactions_reload.py\r\n\r\nWhich iterates over transactions stored in a JSON database, to retrieve the transaction receipt from the node. I need the receipt as it contains information about whether a transaction failed or not.  On a side note, I find it illogical that I need to go through an additional step to verify that a transaction succeeded.\r\n\r\nSo the transaction hash is real, I've also verified it on public block explorers, and it looks like geth isn't finding transaction for some reason. I've restarted geth with --txlookuplimit 0, and I don't see any significant I/O activity, so it isn't rebuilding an index for example.\r\n\r\nThanks,\r\n\r\nMorten\r\n",
