    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "OK, thanks.\r\n\r\nI think there should be a focus on use-cases where --maxpeers 0 is enabled, as for example I am now on a mobile data network, with limited speed.\r\n\r\nThe node is also crammed along with some other stuff on a light server, and I'm using it for querying and development purposes. Turning down maxpeers to 0, makes the load (CPU, disk, RAM/swap) lighter on the server, and there is more network bandwidth available for other purposes.\r\n\r\nIt would be OK to have maxpeers 4 at night for example.",
